#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:3
msgid "Appendix: Contributing To This Manual"
msgstr "Dodatak: Doprinos ovom priručniku"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:5
msgid ""
"To add materials to this course, you must follow the guidelines in this "
"Appendix. You are not allowed to alter the conditions in this Appendix "
"except for clarification. This is to ensure that the quality and consistency"
" of this manual can be maintained."
msgstr ""
"Da biste dodali materijale u ovaj kurs, morate se pridržavati smernica iz "
"ovog dodatka. Nije vam dozvoljeno da menjate uslove iz ovog dodatka, osim "
"radi pojašnjenja. Time se obezbeđuje da se kvalitet i doslednost ovog "
"priručnika mogu održati."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:10
msgid "Downloading Resources"
msgstr "Preuzimanje resursa"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:12
msgid ""
"The source of this document is available at `GitHub "
"<https://github.com/qgis/QGIS-Documentation>`_. Consult `GitHub.com "
"<https://github.com/>`_ for instructions on how to use the git version "
"control system."
msgstr ""
"Izvor ovog dokumenta dostupan je na `GitHub-u <https://github.com/qgis/QGIS-"
"Documentation>`_. Uputstva za korišćenje sistema za kontrolu verzija git "
"potražite na `GitHub.com <https://github.com/>`_."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:17
msgid "Manual Format"
msgstr "Format priručnika"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:19
msgid ""
"This manual is written using `Sphinx <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/>`_, a Python document generator using the "
"`reStructuredText <https://docutils.sourceforge.io/rst.html>`_ markup "
"language. Instructions on how to use these tools are available on their "
"respective sites."
msgstr ""
"Ovaj priručnik napisan je pomoću alata `Sphinx <https://www.sphinx-"
"doc.org/en/master/>`_, generatora dokumenata u Pythonu koji koristi jezik za"
" obeležavanje `reStructuredText "
"<https://docutils.sourceforge.io/rst.html>`_. Uputstva za korišćenje ovih "
"alata dostupna su na njihovim sajtovima."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:25
msgid "Adding a Module"
msgstr "Dodavanje modula"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:27
msgid "To add a new module:"
msgstr "Da biste dodali novi modul:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:29
msgid ""
"First create a new directory (directly under the  top-level of the "
":file:`qgis-training-manual` directory) with the name of the new module."
msgstr ""
"Prvo napravite novi direktorijum (direktno u korenu direktorijuma "
":file:`qgis-training-manual`) sa nazivom novog modula."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:31
msgid ""
"Under this new directory, create a file called :file:`index.rst`. Leave this"
" file blank for now."
msgstr ""
"U tom novom direktorijumu napravite datoteku pod nazivom :file:`index.rst`. "
"Za sada je ostavite praznu."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:33
msgid ""
"Open the :file:`index.rst` file under the top-level directory. Its first "
"lines are::"
msgstr ""
"Otvorite datoteku :file:`index.rst` u korenom direktorijumu. Njeni prvi "
"redovi su::"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:42
msgid ""
"You will note that this is a list of directory names, followed by the name "
"``index``. This directs the top-level index file to the index files in each "
"directory. The order in which they are listed determines the order they will"
" have in the document."
msgstr ""
"Primetićete da je ovo lista naziva direktorijuma, praćena nazivom ``index``."
" Time se korena indeksna datoteka usmerava ka indeksnim datotekama u svakom "
"direktorijumu. Redosled kojim su navedeni određuje njihov redosled u "
"dokumentu."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:46
msgid ""
"Add the name of your new module (i.e., the name you gave the new directory),"
" followed by ``/index``, to this list, wherever you want your module to "
"appear."
msgstr ""
"Dodajte naziv svog novog modula (tj. naziv koji ste dali novom "
"direktorijumu), praćen sa ``/index``, u ovu listu, na mesto gde želite da se"
" vaš modul pojavi."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:48
msgid ""
"Remember to keep the order of the modules logical, such that later modules "
"build on the knowledge presented in earlier modules."
msgstr ""
"Ne zaboravite da redosled modula bude logičan, tako da se kasniji moduli "
"nadovezuju na znanje izloženo u ranijim modulima."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:50
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Open your new module's own index file (:file:`{module_name}/index.rst`)."
msgstr ""
"Otvorite indeksnu datoteku svog novog modula "
"(:file:`{module_name}/index.rst`)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:51
msgid "Along the top of the page, create the module heading:"
msgstr "Na vrhu stranice napravite naslov modula:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:53
msgid "write a first line of asterisks (``*``)."
msgstr "napišite prvi red zvezdica (``*``)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:54
msgid ""
"Follow this with a line containing the markup phrase ``Module:``, followed "
"by the name of your module."
msgstr ""
"Zatim napišite red koji sadrži oznaku ``Module:``, praćenu nazivom vašeg "
"modula."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:56
msgid "End this off with another line of same number of asterisks."
msgstr "Završite to još jednim redom sa istim brojem zvezdica."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:58
msgid ""
"The underline and the overline should not be shorter than the line "
"containing the module title."
msgstr ""
"Podvučeni i nadvučeni red ne smeju biti kraći od reda koji sadrži naslov "
"modula."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:61
msgid "Leave a line open beneath this."
msgstr "Ostavite jedan prazan red ispod ovoga."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:62
msgid ""
"Write a short paragraph explaining the purpose and content of the module."
msgstr "Napišite kratak pasus koji objašnjava svrhu i sadržaj modula."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:63
msgid "Leave one line open, then add the following text::"
msgstr "Ostavite jedan prazan red, a zatim dodajte sledeći tekst::"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:71
msgid ""
"... where ``lesson1``, ``lesson2``, etc., are the names of your planned "
"lessons."
msgstr ""
"... gde su ``lesson1``, ``lesson2`` itd. nazivi vaših planiranih lekcija."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:73
msgid "The module-level index file will look like this:"
msgstr "Indeksna datoteka na nivou modula izgledaće ovako:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:90
msgid "Adding a Lesson"
msgstr "Dodavanje lekcije"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:92
msgid "To add a lesson to a new or existing module:"
msgstr "Da biste dodali lekciju u novi ili postojeći modul:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:94
msgid "Open the module directory."
msgstr "Otvorite direktorijum modula."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:95
msgid ""
"Open the :file:`index.rst` file (created above in the case of new modules)."
msgstr ""
"Otvorite datoteku :file:`index.rst` (napravljenu gore u slučaju novih "
"modula)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:96
msgid ""
"Ensure that the name of the planned lesson is listed underneath the "
":file:`toctree` directive, as shown above."
msgstr ""
"Uverite se da je naziv planirane lekcije naveden ispod direktive "
":file:`toctree`, kao što je prikazano gore."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:98
msgid "Create a new file under the module directory."
msgstr "Napravite novu datoteku u direktorijumu modula."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:99
msgid ""
"Name this file exactly the same as the name you provided in the module's "
":file:`index.rst` file, and add the extension :file:`.rst`."
msgstr ""
"Nazovite ovu datoteku tačno isto kao naziv koji ste naveli u datoteci "
":file:`index.rst` modula i dodajte ekstenziju :file:`.rst`."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:102
msgid ""
"For editing purposes, a :file:`.rst` file works exactly like a normal text "
"file (:file:`.txt`)."
msgstr ""
"Za potrebe uređivanja, datoteka :file:`.rst` funkcioniše potpuno isto kao "
"obična tekstualna datoteka (:file:`.txt`)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:105
msgid ""
"To begin writing the lesson, write the markup phrase ``Lesson``, followed by"
" the lesson name."
msgstr ""
"Da biste počeli da pišete lekciju, napišite oznaku ``Lesson``, praćenu "
"nazivom lekcije."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:107
msgid ""
"In the next line, write a line of equal signs (``=``), not shorter than the "
"lesson title."
msgstr ""
"U sledećem redu napišite red znakova jednakosti (``=``), ne kraći od naslova"
" lekcije."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:108
msgid "Leave a line open after this."
msgstr "Ostavite jedan prazan red nakon ovoga."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:109
msgid "Write a short description of the lesson's intended purpose."
msgstr "Napišite kratak opis namene lekcije."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:110
msgid ""
"Include a general introduction to the subject matter. See the existing "
"lessons in this manual for examples."
msgstr ""
"Uključite opšti uvod u temu. Za primere pogledajte postojeće lekcije u ovom "
"priručniku."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:112
msgid "Beneath this, start a new paragraph, beginning with this phrase::"
msgstr "Ispod ovoga započnite novi pasus, koji počinje ovom frazom::"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:116
msgid "Briefly explain the intended outcome of completing this lesson."
msgstr "Ukratko objasnite željeni ishod ove lekcije."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:117
msgid ""
"If you can't describe the goal of the lesson in one or two sentences, "
"consider breaking the subject matter up into multiple lessons."
msgstr ""
"Ako ne možete da opišete cilj lekcije u jednoj ili dve rečenice, razmislite "
"o deljenju teme na više lekcija."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:120
msgid ""
"Each lesson will be subdivided into multiple sections, which will be "
"addressed next."
msgstr ""
"Svaka lekcija biće podeljena na više odeljaka, o čemu je reč u nastavku."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:123
msgid "Adding a Section"
msgstr "Dodavanje odeljka"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:125
msgid "There are two types of sections: \"follow along\" and \"try yourself\"."
msgstr "Postoje dve vrste odeljaka: „prati korake“ i „probajte sami“."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:127
msgid ""
"A \"follow along\" section is a detailed set of directions intended to teach"
" the reader how to use a given aspect of QGIS. This is typically done by "
"giving click-by-click directions as clearly as possible, interspersed with "
"screenshots."
msgstr ""
"Odeljak „prati korake“ je detaljan skup uputstava namenjen da čitaoca nauči "
"kako da koristi određeni deo QGIS-a. To se obično radi davanjem uputstava "
"klik po klik, što jasnije moguće, propraćenih snimcima ekrana."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:131
msgid ""
"A \"try yourself\" section gives the reader a short assignment to try by "
"themselves. It is usually associated with an entry in the answer box "
"beneath, which will show or explain how to complete the assignment, and will"
" show the expected outcome if possible."
msgstr ""
"Odeljak „probajte sami“ daje čitaocu kratak zadatak da ga sam uradi. Obično "
"je povezan sa unosom u polju sa odgovorom ispod, koje pokazuje ili "
"objašnjava kako zadatak da se uradi i, ako je moguće, prikazuje očekivani "
"ishod."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:136
msgid ""
"Every section comes with a difficulty level. An easy section is denoted by "
"``★☆☆``, moderate by ``★★☆``, and advanced by ``★★★``."
msgstr ""
"Svaki odeljak ima nivo težine. Lak odeljak označava se sa ``★☆☆``, srednji "
"sa ``★★☆``, a napredni sa ``★★★``."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:140
msgid "Adding a \"follow along\" section"
msgstr "Dodavanje odeljka „prati korake“"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:142
#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:158
msgid ""
"To start this section, write the markup phrase of the intended difficulty "
"level (as shown above)."
msgstr ""
"Da biste započeli ovaj odeljak, napišite oznaku željenog nivoa težine (kao "
"što je prikazano gore)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:144
msgid "Leave a space and then write ``Follow Along:``."
msgstr "Ostavite razmak, a zatim napišite ``Follow Along:``."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:145
msgid ""
"Leave another space and write the name of the section (use only an initial "
"capital letter, as well as capitals for proper nouns)."
msgstr ""
"Ostavite još jedan razmak i napišite naziv odeljka (koristite veliko slovo "
"samo na početku, kao i za vlastite imenice)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:147
#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:161
msgid ""
"In the next line, write a line of minuses/dashes (``-``), not shorter than "
"the section title."
msgstr ""
"U sledećem redu napišite red crtica (``-``), ne kraći od naslova odeljka."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:148
msgid ""
"Write a short introduction to the section, explaining its purpose. Then give"
" detailed (click-by-click) instructions on the procedure to be demonstrated."
msgstr ""
"Napišite kratak uvod u odeljak, objašnjavajući njegovu svrhu. Zatim dajte "
"detaljna uputstva (klik po klik) o postupku koji se prikazuje."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:150
msgid ""
"In each section, include internal links, external links and screenshots as "
"needed."
msgstr ""
"U svakom odeljku uključite interne veze, spoljne veze i snimke ekrana po "
"potrebi."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:151
msgid ""
"Try to end each section with a short paragraph that concludes it and leads "
"naturally to the next section, if possible."
msgstr ""
"Pokušajte da svaki odeljak završite kratkim pasusom koji ga zaokružuje i "
"prirodno vodi ka sledećem odeljku, ako je moguće."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:155
msgid "Adding a \"try yourself\" section"
msgstr "Dodavanje odeljka „probajte sami“"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:160
msgid "Leave a space and then write ``Try Yourself:``."
msgstr "Ostavite razmak, a zatim napišite ``Try Yourself:``."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:162
msgid ""
"Explain the exercise that you want the reader to complete. Refer to previous"
" sections, lessons or modules if necessary."
msgstr ""
"Objasnite vežbu koju želite da čitalac uradi. Uputite na prethodne odeljke, "
"lekcije ili module ako je potrebno."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:164
msgid ""
"Include screenshots to clarify the requirements if a plain textual "
"description is not clear."
msgstr ""
"Uključite snimke ekrana da biste razjasnili zahteve ako običan tekstualni "
"opis nije dovoljno jasan."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:167
msgid ""
"In most cases, you will want to provide an answer regarding how to complete "
"the assignment given in this section. To do so, you will need to create and "
"feed an answer block beneath the instructions."
msgstr ""
"U većini slučajeva želećete da date odgovor o tome kako da se uradi zadatak "
"dat u ovom odeljku. Za to ćete morati da napravite i popunite blok sa "
"odgovorom ispod uputstava."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:171
msgid "First, create the custom collapsible widget that contains the answer::"
msgstr "Prvo napravite prilagođeni sklopivi vidžet koji sadrži odgovor::"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:176
msgid ""
"Keeping an indentation with regard to the above block, write the "
"instructions on how to complete the assignment, using links and images where"
" needed."
msgstr ""
"Zadržavajući uvlačenje u odnosu na gornji blok, napišite uputstva o tome "
"kako da se zadatak uradi, koristeći veze i slike po potrebi."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:181
msgid "Add a Conclusion"
msgstr "Dodavanje zaključka"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:183
msgid "To end a lesson:"
msgstr "Da biste završili lekciju:"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:185
msgid ""
"Write the phrase ``In Conclusion``, followed by a new line of minuses/dashes"
" (``-``)."
msgstr "Napišite frazu ``In Conclusion``, praćenu novim redom crtica (``-``)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:186
msgid ""
"Write a conclusion for the lesson, explaining which concepts have been "
"covered in the lesson."
msgstr ""
"Napišite zaključak lekcije, objašnjavajući koji su pojmovi obrađeni u "
"lekciji."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:189
msgid "Add a Further Reading Section"
msgstr "Dodavanje odeljka za dalje čitanje"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:191
msgid "This section is optional."
msgstr "Ovaj odeljak je opcion."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:193
msgid ""
"Write the phrase ``Further Reading``, followed by a new line of "
"minuses/dashes (``-``)."
msgstr ""
"Napišite frazu ``Further Reading``, praćenu novim redom crtica (``-``)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:195
msgid "Include links to appropriate external websites."
msgstr "Uključite veze ka odgovarajućim spoljnim sajtovima."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:198
msgid "Add a What's Next Section"
msgstr "Dodavanje odeljka „Šta je sledeće“"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:200
msgid ""
"Write the phrase ``What's Next?``, followed by a new line of minuses/dashes "
"(``-``)."
msgstr "Napišite frazu ``What's Next?``, praćenu novim redom crtica (``-``)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:201
msgid ""
"Explain how this lesson has prepared students for the next lesson or module."
msgstr ""
"Objasnite kako je ova lekcija pripremila polaznike za sledeću lekciju ili "
"modul."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:202
msgid ""
"Remember to change the \"what's next\" section of the previous lesson if "
"necessary, so that it refers to your new lesson. This will be necessary if "
"you have inserted a new lesson among existing lessons, or after an existing "
"lesson."
msgstr ""
"Ne zaboravite da po potrebi izmenite odeljak „šta je sledeće“ prethodne "
"lekcije, tako da upućuje na vašu novu lekciju. To će biti potrebno ako ste "
"umetnuli novu lekciju među postojeće lekcije ili posle postojeće lekcije."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:208
msgid "Using Markup"
msgstr "Korišćenje oznaka"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:210
msgid ""
"To adhere to the standards of this document, you will need to add standard "
"markup to your text."
msgstr ""
"Da biste se pridržavali standarda ovog dokumenta, moraćete da svom tekstu "
"dodate standardne oznake."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:214
msgid "New concepts"
msgstr "Novi pojmovi"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:216
msgid ""
"If you are explaining a new concept, you will need to write the new "
"concept's name in italics by enclosing it in asterisks (``*``)."
msgstr ""
"Ako objašnjavate novi pojam, naziv tog novog pojma morate napisati kurzivom,"
" tako što ćete ga staviti između zvezdica (``*``)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:224
msgid "Emphasis"
msgstr "Isticanje"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:226
msgid ""
"To emphasize a crucial term which is not a new concept, write the term in "
"bold by enclosing it in double asterisks (``**``)."
msgstr ""
"Da biste istakli ključni termin koji nije novi pojam, napišite termin "
"podebljano tako što ćete ga staviti između dvostrukih zvezdica (``**``)."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:228
msgid ""
"Use this sparingly! If used too much, it can seem to the reader that you are"
" shouting or being condescending."
msgstr ""
"Koristite ovo štedljivo! Ako se koristi previše, čitaocu može delovati da "
"vičete ili da ste snishodljivi."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:238
msgid "Images"
msgstr "Slike"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:240
msgid ""
"When adding an image, save it to an :file:`img` folder next to the lesson "
"file."
msgstr ""
"Kada dodajete sliku, sačuvajte je u folder :file:`img` pored datoteke "
"lekcije."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:241
msgid "Include it in the document like this::"
msgstr "Uključite je u dokument ovako::"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:246
msgid "Remember to leave a line open above and below the image markup."
msgstr "Ne zaboravite da ostavite prazan red iznad i ispod oznake za sliku."

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:249
msgid "Internal links"
msgstr "Interne veze"

#: ../../docs/training_manual/appendix/contribute.rst:251
msgid ""
"To create an anchor for a link, write the following line above the place "
